A good father keeps the mother happy
so she doesn't drive the kids crazy.

744
01:14:01,329 --> 01:14:05,288
She called me a big kid . . .
She's probably right.

745
01:14:05,449 --> 01:14:09,442
You're one year old
and my best friend in the world.

746
01:14:09,609 --> 01:14:13,204
Anyway . . .

747
01:14:15,569 --> 01:14:19,960
- I'll miss you.
- Don't be sad. Here, take this.

748
01:14:25,089 --> 01:14:31,358
- No, I want you to have it.
- Okay, thanks.

749
01:14:31,529 --> 01:14:34,919
He'll take good care of you.

750
01:14:39,969 --> 01:14:44,326
- We're going to see Daddy today.
- I was just thinking about James.

751
01:14:44,489 --> 01:14:50,359
- The blue or the lamb?
- They both look pretty lame.

752
01:14:50,529 --> 01:14:54,158
- The lamb?
- Not lamb, lame!

753
01:14:54,329 --> 01:14:58,641
Please don't make me wear clothes
with animals on them.

754
01:14:58,809 --> 01:15:03,121
I don't like this.
It makes me look stupid.

755
01:15:03,289 --> 01:15:08,568
- You look great.
- I feel like a retard.

756
01:15:12,249 --> 01:15:15,798
Look at this room.
Look at these guys.

757
01:15:15,969 --> 01:15:19,166
I bet I could take those apart.

758
01:15:19,329 --> 01:15:24,608
Little metal things . . . I'll stick
them in those little holes.

759
01:15:25,489 --> 01:15:30,643
Mollie, hi. This must be Mikey.

760
01:15:30,809 --> 01:15:35,758
Hiya, fella. What are you doing?

761
01:15:35,929 --> 01:15:40,002
- Aren't you a handsome . . .
- Milk in the eye.

762
01:15:40,169 --> 01:15:42,364
Bull's-eye!

763
01:15:42,529 --> 01:15:47,444
It's all right.
It's just milk, it won't stain.

764
01:15:48,889 --> 01:15:54,919
- He's beautiful. He looks like you.
- A lot of people say that.

765
01:15:55,089 --> 01:16:00,322
I know the circumstances
you had him under were terrible.

766
01:16:00,489 --> 01:16:05,279
- But I know it wasn't a mistake.
- I bet he's glad to hear that.

767
01:16:05,449 --> 01:16:09,488
You will never escape me.

768
01:16:09,649 --> 01:16:13,437
- Mikey, don't do that!
- What did I do?

769
01:16:13,609 --> 01:16:20,959
Some people don't have the strength
to get out certain situations.

770
01:16:21,129 --> 01:16:25,042
What are you trying to say?
Mikey, don't touch that.

771
01:16:25,209 --> 01:16:31,159
I'm saying I still love you
and I still want you.

772
01:16:31,329 --> 01:16:37,279
- And what about Mikey?
- Count on me. Whatever he needs.

773
01:16:38,329 --> 01:16:40,718
He needs a father.

774
